items.description: Oct 26: Durisic is away from the team and out for Monday's game against the Bulls.
Oct 9: The Celtics have not ruled Tatum (Achilles) out for the 2025-26 season, ESPN's Shams Charania reported on the Pat McAfee Show on Thursday.
Oct 25: Wolf (ankle) has been ruled out for Sunday's game against the Spurs, Sharif Phillips-Keaton of USA Today reports.
Oct 19: Highsmith (knee) experienced swelling during rehab and will re-evaluated in eight weeks, Brett Siegel of ClutchPoints.com reports.
Oct 20: The Bulls announced Monday that White (calf) will be re-evaluated in two weeks.
Oct 18: Collins will be sidelined for at least four weeks due to a left wrist fracture, Mike McGraw of the Chicago Daily Herald reports.
Oct 15: Garland (toe) participated in a scrimmage with contact Tuesday, Chris Fedor of Cleveland.com reports.
Sep 30: Strus (foot) is no longer wearing a walking boot on Tuesday, but still has a lengthy recovery process ahead, Chris Fedor of The Cleveland Plain Dealer reports.
Oct 26: Gafford (ankle) has been ruled out for Sunday's game against the Raptors.
Oct 25: Exum (knee) has been ruled out for Sunday's game against the Raptors.

note: Source: Ball Don't Lie player injuries feed. Displaying the 10 most relevant recent reports.
